---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumb from '../components/Breadcrumb.astro';
import { siteConfig } from '../data/site-config';

const breadcrumbs = [
  { label: 'Home', href: '/' },
  { label: 'Privacy Policy', href: '/privacy-policy' },
];
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy | Integer Training Online Courses UK"
  description="Integer Training's privacy and data protection policy explains how we collect, store, and use your personal data in compliance with the Data Protection Act 2018 and UK GDPR."
>
  <Breadcrumb items={breadcrumbs} />

  <section class="py-24 lg:py-32">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <h1 class="font-display font-bold text-4xl md:text-5xl text-neutral-900 mb-8">Data Protection & Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="text-neutral-500 text-sm mb-6">Last updated: March 2026</p>

      <a
        href="/policies/data-protection-policy.pdf"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
        class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-primary-500 hover:text-primary-600 font-medium text-sm mb-12 transition-colors duration-300"
      >
        <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-red-500" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
          <path d="M14 2H6a2 2 0 00-2 2v16a2 2 0 002 2h12a2 2 0 002-2V8z" />
          <polyline points="14 2 14 8 20 8" />
          <line x1="12" y1="18" x2="12" y2="12" />
          <line x1="9" y1="15" x2="12" y2="18" />
          <line x1="15" y1="15" x2="12" y2="18" />
        </svg>
        Download Full Policy PDF
      </a>

      <div class="prose prose-lg text-neutral-600 space-y-8">
        <section>
          <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-2xl text-neutral-900 mb-4">1. Introduction</h2>
          <p>{siteConfig.companyName} is committed to preserving the privacy of its learners and employees and to complying with the Data Protection Act 2018 and the UK General Data Protection Regulation (UK GDPR). This policy sets out how we collect, use, store and protect personal information.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-2xl text-neutral-900 mb-4">2. Data Protection Principles</h2>
          <p>We adhere to the following data protection principles. Personal data shall be:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
            <li>Obtained and processed fairly and lawfully</li>
            <li>Obtained for a specified and lawful purpose</li>
            <li>Adequate, relevant and not excessive for those purposes</li>
            <li>Accurate and kept up to date</li>
            <li>Not kept for longer than is necessary</li>
            <li>Processed in accordance with data subjects' rights</li>
            <li>Kept safe from unauthorised access, accidental loss or destruction</li>
            <li>Not transferred to a country outside the European Economic Area without adequate protection</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-2xl text-neutral-900 mb-4">3. Data Controller</h2>
          <p>The data controller is {siteConfig.companyName}, registered at {siteConfig.address.street}, {siteConfig.address.city}, {siteConfig.address.zip}. The designated Data Protection Coordinator is the Operations Manager, Sandeep Dawar.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-2xl text-neutral-900 mb-4">4. Information We Collect</h2>
          <p>We may collect the following categories of personal data:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
            <li>General personal details such as name, address, telephone number, and email address</li>
            <li>Class attendance records</li>
            <li>Course work marks and grades</li>
            <li>Notes of personal supervision</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-4">Sensitive personal data -- including information about health, sexual orientation, political or religious views, trade union membership, and ethnicity -- is only collected where the individual has given explicit consent and it is necessary for a lawful purpose.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-2xl text-neutral-900 mb-4">5. Data Sharing</h2>
          <p>{siteConfig.companyName} will not release staff or learner data to third parties except to relevant statutory bodies as required by law. In all other circumstances, consent will be obtained from the individual before any personal data is shared with a third party.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-2xl text-neutral-900 mb-4">6. Your Rights</h2>
          <p>Under the Data Protection Act 2018 and UK GDPR, you have the following rights:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
            <li><strong>Right to access your data:</strong> You may submit a Standard Request Form to access the personal data we hold about you. We will respond within 21 days of receiving the request.</li>
            <li><strong>Right to be forgotten:</strong> You may request that your personal data be erased. We will respond within one month of receiving the request.</li>
            <li><strong>Subject consent:</strong> Where we process data based on your consent, you have the right to withdraw that consent at any time.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-2xl text-neutral-900 mb-4">7. Data Retention</h2>
          <p>We retain personal data for as long as necessary for the purpose it was collected. Specific retention periods include:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
            <li>Personnel files and training records: 6 years after employment ends</li>
            <li>Application forms (unsuccessful candidates): 6 months</li>
            <li>Wage and salary records: 6 years</li>
            <li>Student records: at least 6 years from the end of the academic year</li>
            <li>Health records: for the duration of employment</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-2xl text-neutral-900 mb-4">8. Security</h2>
          <p>We take appropriate technical and organisational measures to protect personal data, including:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
            <li>Data is kept in lockable storage when in physical form</li>
            <li>All ICT equipment is password-protected</li>
            <li>Data files containing personal information must be password-protected</li>
            <li>Paper records containing personal data are shredded when no longer required</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-2xl text-neutral-900 mb-4">9. Compliance</h2>
          <p>Any breach of this data protection policy may lead to disciplinary action and, in serious cases, could result in criminal prosecution under the Data Protection Act 2018.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-2xl text-neutral-900 mb-4">10. Contact</h2>
          <p>For any data protection enquiries, to exercise your rights, or to report a concern, contact the Data Protection Coordinator:</p>
          <ul class="list-none pl-0 space-y-1 mt-4">
            <li><strong>Data Protection Coordinator:</strong> Sandeep Dawar (Operations Manager)</li>
            <li><strong>Address:</strong> {siteConfig.companyName}, {siteConfig.address.street}, {siteConfig.address.city}, {siteConfig.address.state}, {siteConfig.address.zip}</li>
            <li><strong>Phone:</strong> {siteConfig.phone}</li>
            <li><strong>Email:</strong> {siteConfig.email}</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-4">You also have the right to lodge a complaint with the Information Commissioner's Office (ICO) at <a href="https://ico.org.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-primary-500 hover:text-primary-600 transition-colors duration-300">ico.org.uk</a>.</p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
